result.adr_address: 28 Yun Ping Rd, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 28 Yun Ping Rd, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: Futago HK

reviews.text:
Upscale Japanese bbq in the Sogo area.  Depending on what you order, food is grilled by the staff to perfection right in front of you on the little grill.  Highly recommend the grilled crab innards, yum.  Prices are on the high side and portions are fairly small, but the taste and service definitely make up for it.  

Important note, there's no restrooms inside the restaurant, you'd have to go to the neighboring mall to use the facilities.

A nice yakiniku restaurant which seems to be a Japanese and Korean hybrid. Beef is really good and better than pork and chicken. Staff are friendly and energetic where you can shout together with them.

Futago is awesome place for yakiniku.  Although is relatively pricey, but they also come with great food, friendly staffs and great atmosphere.
Most of their time are full, and almost not accept any walkin, so it is recommended that you book here in advance.
And the decoration is new, they have a small stove on the table, and its good enough for your meat.  
You can cook it yourself or with the help from staffs.  And staffs will actively cook it for your for some of their dishes.  And even for those you cook by yourself, staffs will still provide advice on how to cook it with the best.
And they atmosphere is great, as staffs are helpful, and love to talk to customers about how to cook it well
Highly recommend, fresh meat and excellent service
The best Japanese bbq with a very reasonable price!!
